-- Russia Grain Sales Rose 16% Last Year, Statistical Service Says
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2012-02-08T13:45:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/russia-grain-sales-rose-16-last-year-statistical-service-says.html
Russia  sold 57.3 million metric tons
of grain for exports and domestically in 2011, 16 percent more
than a year earlier, the Federal State Statistics Service said.  Sales by large commercial agricultural companies rose 12
percent to 44.2 million tons of grain last year, the service,
known as Rosstat, said today in an e-mailed statement. The rest
of the grain trade was done by small farmers and villagers, it
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
